---

Why CC BY-SA 4.0 and not MIT?

This repository contains documentation and knowledge, not source code.
CC BY-SA 4.0 is designed for creative works and documentation, while MIT
is designed for software. CC BY-SA 4.0 ensures that:

1. Attribution is preserved — users must credit the original work.
2. Derivatives remain open — any adapted playbook must also be shared openly.
3. The commons grows — improvements benefit everyone.

If you build on this playbook inside your organization, you are encouraged
(but not legally required) to contribute improvements back.

---

The examples/ directory contains reference implementations that illustrate
how to apply this playbook. Any code within those examples is also licensed
under CC BY-SA 4.0.
